      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "tone": "info",
          "title": "Also",
          "body": "1 medium online, peeled and thinly sliced."
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Trim away any fat from the steak, place into a plastic (food grade) bag and tenderise. I do this hitting the bag a number of times with a rolling pin."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Take the steak out of the bag and slice into thin strips, not more than 1cm wide (I usually do more like ½ cm wide - thinner means they get more covered in the sauce!)"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the olive oil, butter, onion and mushrooms to a frying pan and fry until the onions are soft and mushrooms caramelising."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the steak and fry until the meat is browned."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the paprika and stir to combine (if needed, temporarily remove from the heat while you stir so it doesn’t catch. The paprika will burn relatively easily so you need to stir it in quickly)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the beef stock and simmer for a few minutes until about half of it has absorbed or evaporated."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Add the cream fraiche and mix in."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Simmer for another 3-4 mins, stirring frequently, for the creme fraiche to simmer down. Serve."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking — food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one — gentler than full blast."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Vegetarian swap: replace meat with mushrooms, lentils, or beans — adjust seasoning to compensate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Spice version: a pinch of chilli flakes or cracked black pepper at the end shifts the dish without losing its character."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about — the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
